Quote: [Still higher we enter the sub-alpine scrub, ... Here the vegetation, though dense, assumes a dwarf and stunted appearance, and consists largely of shrubby veronicas, white and yellow-flowered daisy trees [fn <i>Olearia</i> and <i>Senecio.</i>], and various curious representatives of the heath order, amongst which ... the quaint <i>Dracophyllum traversii</i>, a much-branched tree, whose branches end each in a tuft of stiff foliage, reminding one of the crown of a pine-apple.]
